---
import DocsLayout from "../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";

const prov = 'provider "oci" ' + "{\n" +
    "  region           = var.region\n" +
    "  tenancy_ocid     = var.tenancy_ocid\n" +
    "  user_ocid        = var.user_ocid\n" +
    "  private_key_path = var.private_key_path\n" +
    "  fingerprint      = var.fingerprint\n" +
    "}";
---

<DocsLayout title="OpenTofu OCI Provider - ITOps Automation Lab" activePage="opentofu-oci"
    lang="en"
    prev={{ label: "Architecture OCI", href: "/en/aiops-lab/phase-9/architecture" }}
    next={{ label: "OCI Vault vs HashiCorp", href: "/en/aiops-lab/phase-9/oci-vault-vs-hashicorp" }}
>
    <div class="docs-page">
        <div class="h"><div class="h__top"><div class="h__badge">Phase 9.1</div><span class="h__time">OpenTofu OCI</span></div><h1 class="h__title">OpenTofu OCI Provider<span class="h__accent"> · oracle/oci</span></h1><p class="h__sub">El provider oracle/oci ~> 6.0 de OpenTofu provisiona toda la infraestructura de Oracle Cloud: VCN, NSG, VMs Ampere A1, OCI Vault y Object Storage. Mismo workflow init → plan → apply que el provider de Kubernetes local.</p></div>

        <div class="sec">
            <div class="sec__h"><span class="sec__num">01</span><h2 class="sec__h2">Autenticacion OCI</h2></div>
            <p class="sec__lead">OCI usa API keys para autenticar. Se generan en la consola y se pasan como variables sensibles a OpenTofu via terraform.tfvars.</p>
            <div class="cb"><div class="cb__h"><span class="cb__file">tofu/oracle/provider.tf</span></div>
                <pre><code>{prov}</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p class="sec__text">Las variables tenancy_ocid, user_ocid y fingerprint estan marcadas como sensitive = true. OpenTofu no las muestra en logs ni en el output de plan. Se almacenan en terraform.tfvars que esta en .gitignore.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sec">
            <div class="sec__h"><span class="sec__num">02</span><h2 class="sec__h2">Recursos Creados</h2></div>
            <p class="sec__lead">Cinco archivos .tf definen la infraestructura completa de Oracle Cloud.</p>
            <div class="grid2">
                <div class="sc"><div class="sc__val">network.tf</div><div class="sc__desc">VCN 10.0.0.0/16, subnet publica, Internet Gateway, route table</div></div>
                <div class="sc"><div class="sc__val">main.tf</div><div class="sc__desc">2 NSGs con reglas least-privilege para bastion y k3s</div></div>
                <div class="sc"><div class="sc__val">compute.tf</div><div class="sc__desc">2 VMs Ampere A1 ARM64, imagen Rocky 9, cloud-init</div></div>
                <div class="sc"><div class="sc__val">object_storage.tf</div><div class="sc__desc">Bucket Loki (S3-compatible, NoPublicAccess)</div></div>
                <div class="sc"><div class="sc__val">vault.tf</div><div class="sc__desc">OCI Vault + master key AES-256 + secrets placeholder</div></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sec sec--cta">
            <div class="cta"><div class="cta__content"><h3 class="cta__title">Siguiente: OCI Vault vs HashiCorp</h3><p class="cta__desc">Comparacion entre Vault self-hosted en el lab y OCI Vault gestionado en la nube.</p></div><a href="/en/aiops-lab/phase-9/oci-vault-vs-hashicorp" class="cta__btn"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21.5 2v6h-6M2.5 22v-6h6M2 11.5a10 10 0 0118.8-4.3M22 12.5a10 10 0 01-18.8 4.2"/></svg>OCI Vault vs HashiCorp</a></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
    .docs-page { max-width: 740px; }
